SubjectOrder Fixing September 18, 2009 as the Date of the Coming into Force of Certain Sections of the Acts
PrecisOrder fixing September 18, 2009 as the date on which certain sections of An Act to establish the Wage Earner Protection Program Act, to amend the Bankruptcy and Insolvency Act and the Companies' Creditors Arrangement Act and to make consequential amendments to other Acts come into force. c.47, 2005 The order also fixes September 18, 2009 as the date on which certain subsections and sections of An Act to amend the Bankruptcy and Insolvency Act, the Companies' Creditors Arrangement Act, the Wage Earner Protection Program Act and chapter 47 of the Statutes of Canada, 2005, come into force. c.36, 2007
